 Write a program in QBASIC.

a. To enter the radius of a circle and calculate and display its area:

CLS
INPUT "Enter the radius of the circle: ", R
A = 3.14159 * R * R
PRINT "The area of the circle is: "; A
END

b. To input any number and check whether the number is even or odd:

CLS
INPUT "Enter any number: ", N
IF N MOD 2 = 0 THEN
PRINT "The number is even."
ELSE
PRINT "The number is odd."
END IF
END
